      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Oct 8 article about flamboyance of Pierre Elliott Trudeau, the late Canadian prime minister, misspelled surname of an author mentioned</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article in Sunday Styles this week about the flamboyance of Pierre Elliott Trudeau, the late Canadian prime minister, misspelled the surname of an author who is the wife of a former Canadian ambassador to Washington and who recently wrote about Mr. Trudeau's personal attractiveness. She is Sondra Gotlieb, not Gottlieb.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>An article in Sunday Styles this week about the flamboyance of Pierre Elliott Trudeau, the late Canadian prime minister, misspelled the surname of an author who is the wife of a former Canadian ambassador to Washington and who recently wrote about Mr. Trudeau's personal attractiveness. She is Sondra Gotlieb, not Gottlieb.</p>
      </block>
